The 8-year-old marriage of actress Yewande Adekoya to Abiodun Ishola Thomas is going through turbulent times. A chat between Yewande and an undisclosed personality showed that all is not well between the actress and her husband. Multiple reports claim that the marriage, which has produced two children, is almost hitting the rocks after Abiodun moved out of the matrimonial home. In the chat, which was obtained and posted by Goldmyne on Instagram, Yewande lamented how her husband had continued to abuse her emotions. The actress- cum- producer also alleged that Abiodun is a control freak, who is temperamental and unaccountable   Nobody should suffer in the name of Christ – Mary…     ‘How my mother inspired Veekee James brand’     Nollywood actors, producer harp on well researched scripts…   Though the couple has been officially married for eight years, they have been together for 14 years. Yewande further noted that all she wanted from Abidoun was to respect and show her unconditional love. The actress also hinted that for many years in their marriage, she has been the financial backbone with Abiodun refusing to contribute to the running of the house. “For 14 years, I have been our financial backbone. I never for once complained. All I wanted was for him to grow up and act responsibly. I continued to beg him to show me love, treat me right and act responsibly,” she noted in the chat. Until the recent episode, Yewande and Abiodun, who are Nollywood practitioners, were seen as one of the commendable couples in the industry. Abiodun Thomas is yet to respond to the allegations neither has Yewande confirmed nor denylied the crack in their relationship. The development is another actress, Nkechi Blessing and her lover, Opeyemi Falegan quit their relationship of less than two years.